article.headline: Penn 55, Brown 54
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- Dan Moncton scored on a put-back at the buzzer after an offensive rebound and Penn beat Brown 55-54 on Saturday night. The Quakers rallied from a five-point deficit in the final 20 seconds. Trailing 54-49, Zack Rosen hit a layup to cut the lead to 54-51. Rosen then hit two foul shots with 6 seconds left to cut the lead to one. Brown's Tucker Halpern missed a free throw with 5 seconds remaining, Penn rebounded and Zack Gordon missed a 3-pointer before Moncton's heroics. Brown led most of the game and built a 13-point lead at 24-11 after a jumper by Marques Coleman with 5:21 left in the first half. Rosen scored 19 points, Jack Eggleston had 18 and Moncton 11 for the Quakers (2-14, 1-1 Ivy League), who snapped a four-game losing streak. Halpern led the Bears (7-15, 1-3) with 14 points, Matt Mullery added 12 and Garrett Leffelman had 10.
